    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Yes-- this is a legacy convenience wart before the existence of the add/mul/div/sub methods:\n\nhttp://pandas.pydata.org/pandas-docs/stable/dsintro.html#data-alignment-and-arithmetic\n\n```\nIn the special case of working with time series data, if the Series is a TimeSeries \n(which it will be automatically if the index contains datetime objects), and the \nDataFrame index also contains dates, the broadcasting will be column-wise:\n```\n\nTo get consistent cross-sectional demeaning regardless of the index type, you would want to do:\n\n`aapl.sub(aapl.mean(1), axis=0)`\n\nthis means: subtract the cross-sectional mean at each time point from each column. `axis=0` in this context means \"align on the row index\" (vs. `axis=1` being align on the columns) \n"
  },
